      "amount": "1/4 cup",
      "notes": "raw"
    },
    {
      "name": "water",
      "amount": "1 cup",
      "notes": "as needed"
    },
    {
      "name": "olive oil",
      "amount": "4 tbsp",
      "notes": "for oiling pan"
    },
    {
      "name": "coconut milk",
      "amount": "1/2 cup",
      "notes": "optional, rich extra flavor"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 425° F.",
    "Trim broccoli crowns, cut into florets.",
    "Mix fermented jang, brown rice flour, and melted butter in a small bowl.",
    "Add minced garlic, sprinkle of nutritional yeast, salt, and black pepper to the bowl.",
    "Stir sesame seeds into the mixture.",
    "Grease a 9x13 inch baking dish with olive oil.",
    "Add broccoli florets, leaving space between each piece.",
    "Pour the fermented jang mixture over the broccoli.",
    "Add water as needed to prevent over-drying.",
    "Bake for 25 minutes, shaking pan halfway.",
    "If desired, add coconut milk for creamy topping.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with additional sesame seeds.",
    "Optional: top with sliced green onions or crispy tempeh for added texture and flavor.",
    "Note: This recipe can be made with other cruciferous vegetables like cauliflower or Brussels sprouts."
  ],
